  "conditionals": 83,
  "description": "Aerobic respiration in Saccharomyces cerevisiae converts pyruvate to CO2 and H2O through the TCA cycle and electron transport chain, generating significantly more ATP than fermentation. This pathway is repressed under high glucose conditions (Crabtree effect/glucose repression) and activated during diauxic shift or respiratory growth on non-fermentable carbon sources. Mitochondrial function and respiratory gene expression are tightly regulated by oxygen availability and carbon source quality.",
  "id": "yeast_aerobic_respiration",
  "logicGates": {
    "and": 2,
    "not": 5,
    "or": 5
  },
  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    %% Environmental Inputs\n    A[Low Glucose or Non-Fermentable<br/>Carbon Source] --> B[Respiratory Growth Signal]\n    C[Oxygen Available] --> D[Aerobic Condition]\n    E[Ethanol or Glycerol Present] --> F[Alternative Carbon Source]\n    \n    B --> G{OR: Activate<br/>Respiration?}\n    D --> G\n    F --> G\n    \n    G -->|Yes| H[/Derepress Respiratory Genes/]\n    G -->|No| I[Maintain Fermentation]\n    \n    %% SNF1/Snf1 Activation (Glucose Derepression)\n    H --> J[SNF1 Kinase Activation]\n    J --> K[Mig1 Phosphorylation]\n    K --> L[Mig1 Nuclear Export]\n    L --> M[/Relief of Glucose Repression/]\n    \n    %% Respiratory Gene Expression\n    M --> N[HAP2/3/4/5 Complex Activation]\n    N --> O[Cytochrome c Expression CYC1]\n    N --> P[Cytochrome c Oxidase COX Genes]\n    N --> Q[ATP Synthase Genes ATP1-20]\n    N --> R[TCA Cycle Enzyme Genes]\n    \n    %% Pyruvate Entry to Mitochondria\n    O --> S[Functional Respiratory Chain]\n    A --> T[Pyruvate from Glycolysis]\n    T --> U[Pyruvate Carrier MPC1/MPC2]\n    U --> V[Pyruvate in Mitochondrial Matrix]\n    \n    %% Pyruvate Dehydrogenase Complex\n    V --> W{AND: PDH Complex<br/>Assembly?}\n    P --> X[Lipoamide Required]\n    Q --> Y[Coenzyme A Required]\n    X --> W\n    Y --> W\n    \n    W -->|Yes| Z[Pyruvate Dehydrogenase PDA1/PDB1]\n    Z --> AA[Acetyl-CoA + NADH + CO2]\n    \n    %% TCA Cycle Entry\n    AA --> AB[Citrate Synthase CIT1/CIT2/CIT3]\n    AB --> AC[Oxaloacetate + Acetyl-CoA]\n    AC --> AD(\\1)\n    AD --> AE[Aconitase ACO1]\n    AE --> AF(\\1)\n    \n    %% NADH Generation Steps\n    AF --> AG[Isocitrate Dehydrogenase IDH1/IDH2]\n    AG --> AH[\u03b1-Ketoglutarate + NADH + CO2]\n    AH --> AI[\u03b1-Ketoglutarate Dehydrogenase KGD1/KGD2]\n    AI --> AJ[Succinyl-CoA + NADH + CO2]\n    \n    %% GTP Generation\n    AJ --> AK[Succinyl-CoA Synthetase LSC1/LSC2]\n    AK --> AL[Succinate + GTP]\n    AL --> AM[Succinate Dehydrogenase SDH1-4]\n    AM --> AN[Fumarate + FADH2]\n    \n    AN --> AO[Fumarase FUM1]\n    AO --> AP(\\1)\n    AP --> AQ[Malate Dehydrogenase MDH1]\n    AQ --> AR[Oxaloacetate + NADH]\n    \n    %% NADH/FADH2 to Electron Transport Chain\n    AA --> AS[NADH Pool]\n    AH --> AS\n    AJ --> AS\n    AR --> AS\n    \n    AN --> AT[FADH2 Pool]\n    \n    %% Electron Transport Chain\n    AS --> AU[\"Complex I: NADH Dehydrogenase NDE1/NDI1\"]\n    AU --> AV[Ubiquinone Reduced]\n    AT --> AW[\"Complex II: Succinate-Q Reductase\"]\n    AW --> AV\n    \n    AV --> AX[\"Complex III: bc1 Complex QCR2/7/8/9/10\"]\n    AX --> AY[Cytochrome c Reduced]\n    AY --> AZ[\"Complex IV: Cytochrome c Oxidase COX1-15\"]\n    AZ --> BA[H2O Formation]\n    \n    %% Proton Pumping\n    AU --> BB[Protons Pumped to IMS]\n    AX --> BB\n    AZ --> BB\n    \n    BB --> BC[Proton Gradient \u0394pH]\n    BC --> BD[Electrochemical Gradient \u0394\u03c8]\n    \n    %% ATP Synthesis\n    BD --> BE{AND: Gradient +<br/>ATP Synthase?}\n    Q --> BF[F0F1-ATPase Complex]\n    BF --> BE\n    \n    BE -->|Yes| BG[ATP Synthase ATP1-5]\n    BG --> BH[ADP + Pi \u2192 ATP]\n    BH --> BI[~32 ATP per Glucose]\n    \n    %% Oxygen as Terminal Acceptor\n    C --> BJ[O2 to Mitochondria]\n    BJ --> AZ\n    AZ --> BK{Is O2 Available?}\n    BK -->|Yes| BA\n    BK -->|No| BL[/Respiration Halted/]\n    \n    %% Metabolite Export\n    BI --> BM[ATP Export to Cytoplasm]\n    BM --> BN[AAC1/AAC2/AAC3 ADP/ATP Carrier]\n    BN --> BO[ATP Available for Cell]\n    \n    %% Alternative Pathways\n    V --> BP{OR: Alternative<br/>Pyruvate Use?}\n    BP -->|Minor| BQ[/Alanine Aminotransferase/]\n    BP -->|Major| Z\n    \n    %% Regulation Feedback\n    BI --> BR{ATP/ADP Ratio High?}\n    BR -->|Yes| BS[/Inhibit PDH and TCA/]\n    BR -->|No| BT[Maintain Respiration]\n    BS --> BU[Reduced Respiratory Rate]\n    \n    %% Reactive Oxygen Species\n    AV --> BV{OR: Electron<br/>Leakage?}\n    BV -->|Yes| BW[Superoxide O2- Generation]\n    BW --> BX[Sod1/Sod2 Superoxide Dismutase]\n    BX --> BY(\\1)\n    BY --> BZ[Catalase Ctt1]\n    BZ --> CA(\\1)\n    \n    %% Final Products\n    BA --> CB[H2O as Product]\n    AA --> CC[CO2 from PDH]\n    AH --> CD[CO2 from IDH]\n    AJ --> CE[CO2 from KGD]\n    BO --> CF[High ATP Yield]\n    \n    %% Styles\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style B fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style D fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style E fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style F fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style G fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style H fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style I fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style J fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style K fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style L fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style M fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style N fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style O fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style P fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style Q fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style R fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style S fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style T fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style U fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style V fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style W fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style X fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Y fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style Z fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AA fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AB fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AC fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AD fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AE fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AF fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AG fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AH fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AI fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AJ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AK fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AL fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AM fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AN fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AO fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AP fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AQ fill:#